      • MAC_MODE_X99

        public static final int MAC_MODE_X99
        Use the MAC key to perform TDES/AES encryption on BLOCK1, perform bitwise XOR on the encryption result with BLOCK2, and then use TAK to perform TDES/AES encryption, sequentially obtaining an encryption result of 8 bytes (or 16 bytes)
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • MAC_MODE_HFM

        public static final int MAC_MODE_HFM
        Hypercom Fast Mode perform bitwise XOR on BLOCK1 and BLOCK2, and perform bitwise XOR on the XOR result and BLOCK3, sequentially, to obtain an 8-byte (or 16-byte) XOR result. Use TAK to perform TDES/AES encryption on this result
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • MAC_MODE_X919

        public static final int MAC_MODE_X919
        According to the ANSIX9.19 specification BLOCK1 is encrypted using TAK for TDES/AES (only the first 8 bytes (or 16 bytes) of keys are taken), and the encryption result is XOR bit by bit with BLOCK2, followed by TAK for DES encryption. The encryption result is obtained in sequence of 8 bytes (or 16 bytes) until the last time TDES/AES encryption is used
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
